   {:e #blake3 "dcd3cc128250c928aa7ccd7d99d8f0ed33a0bc3fb7296948ed14f8abeda082ba" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Remove innate concepts AND add auto-crystallization during observe. Without innate concepts, the first 3+ observations are uncategorized. Without auto-crystallization, concepts only form at harvest — leaving the agent blind for the entire pre-harvest session.\n\nTWO CHANGES:\n\nCHANGE A — Remove innate seeding from init (init.rs):\nIn init.rs lines 288-327, wrap the innate concept block in a config check:\n  let seed_innate = braid_kernel::config::get_config(live.store(), 'policy.innate-concepts')\n      .map(|v| v == 'true')\n      .unwrap_or(false); // Default: OFF\n  if seed_innate { ... existing innate block ... }\nUpdate output line 325 from 'schemas: components | ...' to 'concepts: emergent (form after 3+ observations)'.\nUpdate status.rs: when concept inventory is empty, show 'concepts: none yet (emerge after 3+ observations)'.\n\nCHANGE B — Auto-crystallization in observe (observe.rs):\nAfter concept assignment (line ~628), if multi_assignments is EMPTY (uncategorized) AND this is NOT the very first observation, check if there are enough uncategorized observations to crystallize:\n\n  // Auto-crystallization: form concepts from accumulated uncategorized observations.\n  if multi_assignments.is_empty() {\n      let obs_emb_attr = Attribute::from_keyword(':exploration/embedding');\n      let concept_ref_attr = Attribute::from_keyword(':exploration/concept');\n      let body_attr = Attribute::from_keyword(':exploration/body');\n      \n      // Count observations with embeddings but no concept assignment.\n      let has_embedding: HashSet<EntityId> = store.datoms()\n          .filter(|d| d.op == Op::Assert && d.attribute == obs_emb_attr)\n          .map(|d| d.entity).collect();\n      let has_concept: HashSet<EntityId> = store.datoms()\n          .filter(|d| d.op == Op::Assert && d.attribute == concept_ref_attr)\n          .map(|d| d.entity).collect();\n      let uncategorized: Vec<EntityId> = has_embedding.difference(&has_concept).copied().collect();\n      \n      if uncategorized.len() >= braid_kernel::concept::MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE {\n          // Collect (entity, embedding, body) tuples for crystallization.\n          // ... same pattern as harvest.rs lines 882-915 ...\n          let new_concepts = braid_kernel::concept::crystallize_concepts(&observations, crystal_threshold, MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE);\n          if !new_concepts.is_empty() {\n              // Transact concept datoms + membership datoms.\n              // Re-run concept assignment for current observation.\n          }\n      }\n  }\n\nUse the calibrated threshold from config for crystallization (not the hardcoded JOIN_THRESHOLD constant — per ADR-FOUNDATION-031).\n\nAfter auto-crystallization, RE-RUN assign_to_concepts_soft for the CURRENT observation so it gets assigned to the freshly-formed concept. Update concept_assignment and multi_assignments variables.\n\nUX FLOW:\n  Obs 1: 'uncategorized (concepts emerge after 3+ observations)' \n  Obs 2: 'uncategorized (2/3 observations toward first concepts)'\n  Obs 3: 'AUTO-CRYSTALLIZED: 1 new concept [data-persistence] from 3 observations. Assigned to data-persistence (sim=0.72).'\n  Obs 4+: Normal concept assignment + discrepancy steering\n\nACCEPTANCE:\n(A) braid init creates 0 innate concepts by default.\n(B) After 3 observations (without harvest), at least 1 concept exists.\n(C) Observation 3 output mentions auto-crystallization.\n(D) Observation 4 gets concept assignment against the auto-crystallized concept.\n(E) braid init with policy.innate-concepts=true still seeds innate concepts.\n(F) harvest.rs crystallization uses calibrated threshold from config.\n(G) All existing tests pass.\n\nFILE: crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/harvest.rs (threshold)" :op :assert}
